**Segments**

The global wellness supplements market can be segmented based on product type, distribution channel, end-user, and geography. Product type segmentation includes dietary supplements, functional/fortified food and beverages, and nutraceuticals. Dietary supplements are further categorized into vitamins, minerals, amino acids, enzymes, botanicals, and others. Functional/fortified food and beverages consist of functional foods, functional beverages, and fortified foods. Nutraceuticals include probiotics, proteins and peptides, omega fatty acids, and others. Distribution channel segmentation comprises supermarkets/hypermarkets, pharmacies, health stores, online retailing, and others. End-user segmentation involves adults, elderly, pregnant women, children, and infants.

